o the loan & privileges desk at green library to receive a library card the privileges desk is open anytime the library is open there is a 25 item limit on borrowing privileges at one time please be aware that students only need to obtain a library card if they wish to check out books access to the building will be granted with a valid id and a confirmation of enrollment letter electronic versions displayed on a smart phone are acceptable if your course duration is between 3 4 weeks students are eligible for building access to the sulair libraries but no borrowing privileges are available for courses of this duration no library card is required for building access students must simply present a confirmation of enrollment letter and a valid government issued id at the library entrance for building access electronic versions of confirmation letter displayed on a smart phone are acceptable if your course duration is less than 3 weeks no library access or borrowing privileges will be provided beyond stanford's courtesy privileges helpful links brief guide to stanford university libraries library policies further info for additional questions on library privileges students are invited to contact the library directly at sulair privileges stanford edu or 650.723 1492 or in person cecil h green library 557 escondido mall stanford ca 94305 sulair stands for stanford university library & academic information resources stanford bookstore textbooks and course materials are available at the stanford bookstore on the lower level in a section designated continuing studies required textbooks and course readers are generally available two weeks prior to the start of the quarter bookstore hours monday through thursday 8 00 am 8 00 pm friday 8 00 am 7 00 pm saturday 9 00 am 6 00 pm sunday 11 00 am 6 00 pm bookstore hours vary throughout the quarter to confirm hours before you visit please visit the stanford bookstore website continuing studies students are eligible to receive a 7 discount on textbook purchases at the stanford bookstore order online you may also order books online visit the bookstore's textbook ordering go to books textbooks select continuing studies as your division and scs as your department order by phone to order by phone and have books mailed to you please call the order department at 650 725 6136 ext 328 or 398 shipping charges will apply returns returns can be made with your receipt through the second week of the quarter new books and course readers must be unmarked and undamaged during the summer quarter course readers may only be returned with your receipt one week from date of purchase 2012 stanford university all rights reserved home site map university policies mla program instructor login help
